node.text:
Ingredients:

Use 2 chicken breasts and garlic aioli
1⁄2 a cup of chicken stock
2 tbsp of unsalted butter
1⁄4 cup of red onion finely diced
2 celery ribs finely diced 1⁄4 cup of craisins
1tbsp of curry powder 1⁄2 tbsp of celery salt
1⁄2 tsp of freshly cracked pepper 1tsp of lemon juice to taste

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees

2. In a shallow baking pan add chicken breasts, butter, onions, season with celery salt and

3. Add a generous amount of pepper.

4. Pour chicken stock on top and cover with foil, bake for approx. 20mins or until internal temp is 165 degrees

5. Once the chicken is done, remove it from the oven and allow it to cool.

6. Chop chicken into small dice.

7. In a medium-size bowl combine chicken, aioli, celery, craisins, curry powder, lemon juice, and additional celery salt and pepper to taste.

8. Add more or less aioli depending on preferred consistency.

9. Adjust seasoning to taste and serve with crackers or as a sandwich

Sure, we love a classic burger, but this sweet and spicy version is a work of edible art thanks to pickled onions, grilled pineapple and a homemade glaze jam-packed with flavor made using your favorite condiments from @heinz, available at @walmart. #ad #heinzartoftheburger 

Shop Now: 
https://prod-retailer.chicoryapp.com/checkout/2RJLz

Ingredients:

1 cup white vinegar
1 cup water
2 tablespoons sugar
1 tablespoon salt
1/2 red onion, thinly sliced in half moons
1 1/2 pounds ground beef
1/4 cup Heinz Ketchup
1/4 cup Heinz Honeyracha
3 tablespoons soy sauce
2 limes
2 teaspoons sesame oil
Salt and pepper
3 tablespoons canola oil, divided
4 canned pineapple rings, drained and patted dry
1/2 cup pickled jalapeños
4 tablespoons Kraft Mayonnaise
4 leaves butter lettuce
4 sweet Hawaiian bread style hamburger buns

Steps:

1. Pickled onions: In a small saucepan, combine the vinegar, water, salt, and sugar. Bring just to a simmer and cook until sugar and salt are dissolved. Place the onions in a jar or glass bowl and pour the vinegar mixture over them. Allow to cool at room temperature, then refrigerate for at least 4 hours before using.

2. Burgers: In a small bowl whisk together the Heinz Ketchup, Heinz HoneyRacha, soy sauce, lime juice and sesame oil. Season with salt and pepper.

3. In a medium bowl, add the ground beef and 3 tablespoons of the ketchup mixture, and mix until combined. Form the meat into 4 patties and season with salt and pepper.

4. Heat a large cast iron skillet over medium high heat, and add 2 tablespoons of oil.

5. Place the burger patties into the skillet and cook for 4 minutes. Flip the burgers and brush with the ketchup glaze. Cook for 2 more minutes, flip, and brush with the glaze again, cooking for an additional 1-3 minutes for medium, or until desired doneness is achieved.

Find the rest of the recipe in the comments!

You got to a pool party & these are on the charcuterie board - What do you do?

Ingredients:

1 tablespoon olive oil
1 onion, finely chopped
3 cloves garlic, minced
1 1/2 pounds russet potatoes, peeled and quartered
1 cup whole milk, divided
5 tablespoons butter, cubed
Sea salt
1 cup fresh breadcrumbs
1/2 cup fresh herbs (thyme, rosemary, parsley), chopped
Zest of 1 lemon
1/4 cup tomato paste
1/4 cup Worcestershire sauce
1 teaspoon Dijon mustard
1 large egg
1/2 cup grated carrots
1 1/3 lbs ground beef
48 slices prosciutto
Freshly grated Parmesan cheese
Freshly ground black pepper, to taste

Steps:

1. Preheat oven 350°F, and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.

2. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.

3. Add in onion and sauté, stirring occasionally until golden, about 8 minutes.

4. Add in garlic and cook, stirring often, 2 minutes more. Remove from heat and let mixture cool slightly.

5. Meanwhile, bring a large pot of salted water to a boil over medium heat.

6. Add in potatoes and cook, uncovered, about 15 minutes or until completely tender. Drain well.

7. Transfer potatoes back to pot and mash until smooth.

8. Add in 3/4 cup milk and butter, and fold in with a spatula until well combined. Liberally season with salt to taste.

9. In a large bowl, mix together breadcrumbs and remaining 1/4 cup milk, and let sit 5 minutes to soften.

10. Add in onion and garlic mixture, along with herbs, lemon zest, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, egg, carrots and ground beef. Season with a large pinch of salt.

11. Place 2 slices of prosciutto in each cup of 2 standard size muffin tins, making sure to fully cover the bottom and the sides, leaving about 1/2 inch overhang on all sides.

12. Firmly press about 1/4 to 1/3 cup ground beef mixture into each prosciutto-lined mold.

13. Bake in oven 20 mins.

14. Remove meatloaves from tins and place on the prepared baking sheet.

15. Top each meatloaf with 3 tbsp mashed potatoes.

16. Grate Parmesan cheese over each meatloaf.

17. Preheat broiler to high and broil for 8 to 10 mins until tops are golden.

18. Serve immediately with roasted tomato jam or ketchup, if desired.

node.title: Finally, meatloaf you can eat on the go!

Ingredients:

3 small red potatoes, halved
1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour
2 teaspoons baking powder
1 teaspoon salt
1/4 cup sliced fresh chives
1/4 cup shredded cheddar cheese, plus more for sprinkling
1/2 cup cold unsalted butter
1 tablespoon butter, melted
3/4 cup buttermilk
1/4 cup unsalted butter
1/4 cup all-purpose flour
1 teaspoon onion salt
2 cups beef broth

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a 10-inch cast-iron skillet.

2. Thinly slice each potato lengthwise without cutting all the way through, leaving them hinged together. Set aside.

3. In a food processor fitted with the blade attachment, combine flour, baking powder, salt, cheese and chives.

4. Add 1/2 cup butter and pulse to a coarse consistency. Add buttermilk while pulsing until the dough comes together.

5. Transfer to the cast-iron skillet, and make 6 wells around the center.

6. Gently press potato halves, flat-side down, into the wells in the biscuit dough. Brush the potatoes and biscuit top with the melted butter.

7. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes until the biscuit dough is golden. Cool slightly, then slice.

8. In a saucepan, heat the butter on medium. Add flour and cook until bubbling, about 2 minutes.

9. Add onion salt and beef broth and cook until thickened. Pour over slices of potato biscuits and serve.

🎥: @tastemadeuk 

Ingredients:

300g cooked macaroni
30g plain flour
30g butter
400ml whole milk
200g cheddar, grated
100g mozzarella, grated
50g parmesan, grated
1 cup yellow cornmeal
90g all-purpose flour
1 heaped tbsp caster sugar
2 tsp baking powder
Salt and freshly ground pepper
1 large egg, lightly beaten
110ml whole milk
2l veg oil for frying

Steps:

1. Melt the butter in a pan and then add the flour and stir straight away. Let this colour slightly and then start pouring in the milk a little at a time, whisking after each pour.

2. Once all added stir through all the cheeses followed by the pasta. Once all well mixed, leave to cool.

3. Divide the mixture into 8 and place onto 8 large pieces of cling film. Shape into sausages, and roll the cling film tightly around it, twisting the ends so nothing escapes. Place in the fridge to harden and cool, and then skewer. Place back in the fridge whilst you start making the batter.

4. Whisk together all the dry ingredients. Whisk the eggs and then add this to the dry ingredients along with the milk. Set aside to thicken slightly, and heat the oil to 180C.

5. Dip the mac and cheese into the batter making sure it’s completely covered. Repeat with the rest placing on a tray as you go.

6. Cook in the hot oil for a few minutes until golden all over. Repeat with the remaining mac and cheese dogs. Blot before serving.

node.title: This mac 'n' cheese is pretending to be a corn dog, and we're not mad.

Ingredients:

1 cup chopped fresh chives
1 bunch scallions, ends trimmed, roughly chopped
1/2 cup olive oil
1/4 cup white cheddar cheese
1/4 cup Parmesan cheese
3/4 cup warm milk
1 packet active dry yeast
1 1/2 cups bread flour
2 teaspoons sea salt
1 cup sour cream
2 teaspoons onion salt

Steps:

1. In a food processor fitted with the blade attachment, pulse chives and scallions to a mince.

2. Add olive oil and pulse to combine. Stir in cheeses, and set aside.

3. Preheat oven to 350 degrees, and prepare a baking sheet with parchment paper.

4. In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm milk. Add the flour and sea salt, and knead well. Cover and let rest for 1 hour.

5. In a small bowl, mix sour cream and onion salt, and divide the mixture in half.

6. On a floured surface, roll out the dough to a 6 x 8-inch rectangle. Spread half the sour cream over the dough. Drizzle the pesto over the sour cream.

7. Roll the dough lengthwise into a large tube. With a sharp knife, cut in half lengthwise to reveal the center. Transfer to the prepared baking sheet, and braid with the open center facing up.

8. Bake for 35 minutes or until golden. Serve warm with remaining sour cream and onion dip.

🎥: @tastemadebr 

Ingredients:

3 avocados
1/2 red onion, chopped
2 tomatoes, chopped
1 Brazilian aji pepper, chopped
1/4 bunch cilantro, chopped
1/2 lime
1, 10 1/2-ounce bag Doritos
1 chicken breast, cut into strips
Salt
1 cup wheat flour
1 tablespoon spicy paprika
1 tablespoon onion powder
2 eggs, lightly beaten
Frying oil

Steps:

1. Cut the avocados, remove the pit (do not discard), remove the peel and chop into cubes.

2. Arrange the chopped avocados in a bowl and add the onion, tomatoes, pepper, cilantro and juice of half a lime. Mix thoroughly, salt to taste, and set aside in the refrigerator. (Tip: Store the guacamole with the core inside to stop avocado from becoming dark.)

3. Into a blender or food processor, add the Doritos. Crush into smaller pieces.

4. Season the chicken with salt.

5. In a bowl, combine the flour, paprika and onion powder.

6. Dip the chicken pieces in wheat flour, then in the beaten eggs, and finally the crushed Doritos.

7. Fry in hot oil until golden and crispy. Drain on paper towels.

8. Serve with guacamole.

Ingredients:

Use 2 chicken breasts and garlic aioli
1⁄2 a cup of chicken stock
2 tbsp of unsalted butter
1⁄4 cup of red onion finely diced
2 celery ribs finely diced 1⁄4 cup of craisins
1tbsp of curry powder 1⁄2 tbsp of celery salt
1⁄2 tsp of freshly cracked pepper 1tsp of lemon juice to taste

Steps:

1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees

2. In a shallow baking pan add chicken breasts, butter, onions, season with celery salt and

3. Add a generous amount of pepper.

4. Pour chicken stock on top and cover with foil, bake for approx. 20mins or until internal temp is 165 degrees

5. Once the chicken is done, remove it from the oven and allow it to cool.

6. Chop chicken into small dice.

7. In a medium-size bowl combine chicken, aioli, celery, craisins, curry powder, lemon juice, and additional celery salt and pepper to taste.

8. Add more or less aioli depending on preferred consistency.

9. Adjust seasoning to taste and serve with crackers or as a sandwich

node.text:
Impress your friends with @littlekalegirl’s kiwi bubble tea. 🥝

🎵: handshakes by @ohnonaliya 

INGREDIENTS:

3 kiwi 🥝 fruits 
2 tablespoons of sugar 
3 tablespoons of water 

STEPS:

1. Heat the sugars and sliced kiwis and water for 1 minute and after which blend it.

2. Add 2 tablespoons of Tapioca powder.

3. Mix it and warm it up until jelly texture forms. (on low heat) 

4. To this, add 1 Cupid  Tapioca powder and mix it.

5. Make little balls and boil them for 20 minutes. When finished, let them sit in hot water for another 20 minutes.

6. Rinse in cold water add honey or maple syrup.

7. Enjoy with ice, kiwi fruit juice and butterfly pea powder lemonade! 

#boba #bubbletea #bobatea #bobalife #tastemademedoit

node.text:
How to make homemade hot sauce (and what to put it on). 

Ingredients:

16 Scallops
16 Shrimps
16 Chipirones (Baby Squid)
16 Squid rings
1 Red onion
4 Fresh hot peppers
1 Onion
1 Garlic clove
1 Cup crushed tomatoes
1/2 Cup Apple Cider Vinegar
1 Tbsp Red Pepper Flakes
1 Lime

Steps:

1. Blend the onion with the hot peppers and garlic clove

2. Pan fry for two minutes and add the crushed tomatoes and the vinegar

3. Simmer for 15 minutes, blend and add the pepper flakes. Put in mason jars and keep in the fridge

4. Grill the skewers and drizzle with the cold hot sauce and lime juice

Sure, we love a classic burger, but this sweet and spicy version is a work of edible art thanks to pickled onions, grilled pineapple and a homemade glaze jam-packed with flavor made using your favorite condiments from @heinz, available at @walmart. #ad #heinzartoftheburger 

Shop Now: 
https://prod-retailer.chicoryapp.com/checkout/2RJLz

Ingredients:

1 cup white vinegar
1 cup water
2 tablespoons sugar
1 tablespoon salt
1/2 red onion, thinly sliced in half moons
1 1/2 pounds ground beef
1/4 cup Heinz Ketchup
1/4 cup Heinz Honeyracha
3 tablespoons soy sauce
2 limes
2 teaspoons sesame oil
Salt and pepper
3 tablespoons canola oil, divided
4 canned pineapple rings, drained and patted dry
1/2 cup pickled jalapeños
4 tablespoons Kraft Mayonnaise
4 leaves butter lettuce
4 sweet Hawaiian bread style hamburger buns

Steps:

1. Pickled onions: In a small saucepan, combine the vinegar, water, salt, and sugar. Bring just to a simmer and cook until sugar and salt are dissolved. Place the onions in a jar or glass bowl and pour the vinegar mixture over them. Allow to cool at room temperature, then refrigerate for at least 4 hours before using.

2. Burgers: In a small bowl whisk together the Heinz Ketchup, Heinz HoneyRacha, soy sauce, lime juice and sesame oil. Season with salt and pepper.

3. In a medium bowl, add the ground beef and 3 tablespoons of the ketchup mixture, and mix until combined. Form the meat into 4 patties and season with salt and pepper.

4. Heat a large cast iron skillet over medium high heat, and add 2 tablespoons of oil.

5. Place the burger patties into the skillet and cook for 4 minutes. Flip the burgers and brush with the ketchup glaze. Cook for 2 more minutes, flip, and brush with the glaze again, cooking for an additional 1-3 minutes for medium, or until desired doneness is achieved.

Find the rest of the recipe in the comments!

Question: Is there such a thing as too much cheese? 

🎥: @tastemadeuk 

Giant Cheese Soufflé

Ingredients:

40g butter, plus extra for greasing
20g dried breadcrumbs
40g plain flour
380ml whole milk
3x garlic cloves, crushed
Fine salt and Pepper
4x eggs
50g gruyere cheese, grated
5g chives, finely chopped

Steps:

1. Melt the butter in a pan. Use some of the melted butter to grease a 15cm souffle ramekin, then add the breadcrumbs. Turning the dish around, coat the sides and base in the breadcrumbs and knock out any excess. Set aside.

2. To the melted butter add the flour and stir till combined and there are no lumps. Cook out this mixture for approximately 2 minutes, and then remove from the heat. Slowly add additions of milk stirring between each to ensure there are no lumps. Once all the milk has been added, add the crushed garlic and return to the heat and gently cook stirring constantly until it has thickened. Once thickened add generous seasoning and transfer to bowl, close covered with cling film to prevent a skin forming, and allow to cool for 10 minutes.

3. Preheat the oven to 180 C fan and place a large baking sheet in the oven.

4. Separate your eggs. Add the yolks to your cooled sauce and stir, then stir in the gruyere cheese.

5. In a separate bowl whisk your egg whites until they form medium to stiff peaks. Add one large spoonful of egg white to your cheese mixture and stir to loosen it. Then add the chopped chives and carefully fold the egg whites in, making sure not to over mix and knock the air out of the mixture.

6. Pour the mixture into prepared ramekin and then carefully run a knife around the top edge of the dish to ensure the souffle gets a good rise in the oven. Place the souffle onto the hot baking tray and close the door quickly. Bake the souffle for 25 - 30 minutes until well risen but there is still a little wobble, or baveuse, in the middle. Serve immediately.

Tiny Carne Asada & Guacamole Never Looked So Good. 🤤

Follow @tinykitchentm for more adorable culinary creations! 

Ingredients:

1 inch piece of skirt steak
1/2 clove garlic, minced
1 slice jalapeño, chopped
4 cilantro leaves, chopped
Salt and pepper
1/4 teaspoon lime juice
1/4 teaspoon orange juice
1 teaspoon oil
1 teaspoon avocado
1 cilantro leaf, chopped
1/4 clove garlic, chopped
1/8 teaspoon onion powder
Lime juice
Pico de gallo
Shredded lettuce

Steps:

1. In a large bowl mix, garlic, jalapeño, cilantro, salt, pepper, lime juice, orange juice and oil. Add steak and marinate 4 to 6 hours.

2. Heat grill and cook steak for 8 minutes. Remove and let rest before slicing.

3. For the guacamole: Add all ingredients to the molcajete and mash to combine.

4. To assemble: Fill a tortilla with carne asada, and top with pico de gallo, guacamole and shredded lettuce.
